IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE IOWA PORK PRODUCERS ASSOCIATION IS AN INDUSTRY INCLUSIVE ORGANIZATION WHOSE MISSION IS TO PROVIDE A UNIFIED VOICE TO PROMOTE AND EDUCATE FOR A SUSTAINABLE, SOCIALLY RESPONSIBLE, PROFITABLE, AND GLOBALLY COMPETITIVE PORK INDUSTRY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE IOWA PORK PRODUCERS ASSOCIATION IS AN INDUSTRY INCLUSIVE ORGANIZATION WHOSE MISSION IS TO PROVIDE A UNIFIED VOICE TO PROMOTE AND EDUCATE FOR A SUSTAINABLE, SOCIALLY RESPONSIBLE, PROFITABLE, AND GLOBALLY COMPETITIVE PORK INDUSTRY.
IRS990.Desc: THE IOWA PORK PRODUCERS ASSOCIATION IS AN INDUSTRY INCLUSIVE ORGANIZATION WHOSE MISSION IS TO PROMOTE, EDUCATE AND PROVIDE A LEADING VOICE FOR A SUSTAINABLE, SOCIALLY RESPONSIBLE, AND GLOBALLY COMPETITIVE PORK INDUSTRY.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: IOWA PORK CONGRESS - ANNUAL MULTI-DAY EVENT TO ADVANCE EDUCATION AND OPERATING EFFICIENCIES OF PORK PRODUCERS. EVENT INCLUDES DISPLAY BOOTHS FOR PORK RELATED VENDORS AND EDUCATIONAL CLASSES FOR MEMBERS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: IOWA STATE FAIR PORK TENT - PROMOTION OF PORK PRODUCTS THROUGH THE SALE OF PORK ENTREES AT THE IOWA STATE FAIR. PRODUCTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO ALMOST ONE MILLION FAIR VISITORS ANNUALLY. EDUCATIONAL DISPLAYS ARE ALSO PROVIDED FOR THE EDUCATION OF FAIR GOERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE ACCOUNTING GUIDANCE FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR MATERIAL TAX POSITIONS AND DETERMINED THAT THERE ARE NO INCOME TAX EFFECTS WITH RESPECT TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ASSOCIATION IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO U.S. FEDERAL OR STATE INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS BY TAX AUTHORITIES ON FILED RETURNS FOR FISCAL YEARS PRIOR TO SEPTEMBER 30, 2020.

RecipientBusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: IA DEPT OF AG & LAND STEWARDS

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ASSOCIATION RECEIVES PERIODIC REPORTS ON STATUS AND RESULTS FROM RECIPIENTS OF RESEARCH GRANTS. OTHER GRANTS AND ASSISTANCE ARE MONITORED THROUGH COMMUNICATION BETWEEN ASSOCIATION STAFF MEMBERS AND THE RECIPIENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A COPY OF THE FORM 990 IS PRESENTED AND REVIEWED BY THE BOARD AT THE SAME TIME THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE REVIEWED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPLIANCE WITH POLICY IS MONITORED AND DETERMINED THROUGH COMPLETION OF AN ANNUAL DISCLOSURE OF POTENTIAL CONFLICTS BY VOTING MEMBERS AS WELL AS OFFICERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CASH AND NON-CASH COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS AFTER AN EVALUATION OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S PERFORMANCE. COMPARABILITY DATA FROM SURVEYS AND INFORMATION FROM SIMILAR POSITIONS IS USED IN DETERMINING COMPENSATION LEVELS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION IS A FIXED AMOUNT EVERY YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE NOT MADE AVAILABLE TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC.
